[[File:The Man of Commerce - Anthropomorphic map.png|thumb|The Man of Commerce, 1889, Rand McNally and Company]] '''Anthropomorphic maps''' are [[map]]s that use [[anthropomorphic]] images. Anthropomorphic maps date back to when [[Sebastian Münster]] used a [[queen regnant|queen]] to depict [[Europe]] in 1570.<ref name="WDL">{{cite web |url = http://www.wdl.org/en/item/6770/ |title = The Man of Commerce |website = [[World Digital Library]] |year = 1889 |accessdate = 2013-07-28 }}</ref> The map, ''The Man of Commerce,'' by Augustus F. McKay is the earliest anthropomorphic map known of in the [[United States]], created in 1889.<ref name="WDL"/>
