==Films==

===''Hannah Montana & Miley Cyrus: Best of Both Worlds Concert''===
''[[Hannah Montana & Miley Cyrus: Best of Both Worlds Concert]]'' is a concert film from [[Walt Disney Pictures]] presented in [[Disney Digital 3-D]]. The [[limited release]] was intended to be for one week, February 1–7, 2008 in the US and Canada with release in other countries later on, but was extended for viewing as long as theaters wanted. [[Walt Disney Pictures|Disney]] announced the concert was filmed in several cities to be theatrically released in the US in February and internationally that month. The film uses [[3-D film|3-D]] glasses.

The opening weekend, February 1–3, 2008, the movie had gross revenue of $31.1&nbsp;million. It was the number one movie of the weekend. Opening in only 638 theaters, it set a record of over $42,000 per theater. It set a record for the highest revenue for a 3-D movie for one weekend.

===''Hannah Montana: The Movie''===
''[[Hannah Montana: The Movie]]'' is the [[musical film|musical]] [[film adaptation]] of the American [[teen sitcom]] ''Hannah Montana''. Filming began in April 2008,<ref name="announce">{{cite web|url=http://community.tvguide.com/blog-entry/TVGuide-News-Blog/Todays-News/Miley-Cyrus-Disney/800032572|title=Miley Cyrus and Disney to make Hannah Montana movie – Today's News: Our Take|author=Anna Dimond|work=[[TV Guide]].com|date=February 5, 2008|accessdate=February 5, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080208124307/http://community.tvguide.com/blog-entry/TVGuide-News-Blog/Todays-News/Miley-Cyrus-Disney/800032572|archivedate=February 8, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref> much of it occurring in [[Columbia, Tennessee]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8345336|title=Filming For Hannah Montana Movie Starts In Columbia|publisher=News Channel 5|date=May 19, 2008|accessdate=May 26, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090114025944/http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8345336|archivedate=January 14, 2009|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and Los Angeles, California,<ref name="GuestCast">{{cite web|url=http://www.news4jax.com/entertainmenttonight/16370198/detail.html|title=Production On 'Hannah Montana: The Movie' Is Underway|author=|publisher=News4Jax|date=May 24, 2008|accessdate=May 24, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080528221246/http://www.news4jax.com/entertainmenttonight/16370198/detail.html|archivedate=May 28, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8391689|title=NewsChannel 5.com – Nashville, Tennessee – 'Hannah Montana' Film Scenes Shot In Cool Springs Mall|author=|publisher=[[WTVF|NewsChannel 5]]|date=May 28, 2008|accessdate=May 28, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080529162454/http://www.newschannel5.com/Global/story.asp?S=8391689|archivedate=May 29, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name="GuestCast3">{{cite web|url=http://www.newschannel5.com/global/story.asp?s=8391689|title=Hannah Montana Film Scenes Shot In Cool Springs Mall|author=|publisher=News Channel 5|date=May 28, 2008|accessdate=May 28, 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080529162454/http://www.newschannel5.com/Global/story.asp?S=8391689|archivedate=May 29, 2008|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and was completed in July 2008.<ref name="FilmingCompleted">{{cite web|url=http://www.timeforkids.com/TFK/kids/news/story/0,28277,1827209,00.html |title=Miley Mania – TFK Kid Reporter Yunhee Hyun talks with Miley Cyrus about her new CD, Breakout |publisher=Time for Kids |accessdate=July 29, 2008 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081005124238/http://www.timeforkids.com/TFK/kids/news/story/0,28277,1827209,00.html |archivedate=October 5, 2008 }}</ref> The film was released on April 10, 2009 in the United States and Canada.<ref name="Release Date">{{cite news|url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117981211.html?categoryid=13&cs=1|title=Disney unveils 2009 schedule – Entertainment News, Film News, Media – Variety|author=|publisher=Variety|date=February 24, 2008|accessdate=February 24, 2008|first=Pamela|last=McClintock|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080226195151/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117981211.html?categoryid=13&cs=1#|archive-date=February 26, 2008|dead-url=no|df=mdy-all}}</ref>

