{{expand language|topic=|langcode=zh|otherarticle=黃碧蓮|date=June 2016}} {{BLP sources|date=June 2016}} '''Linna Huynh''' ({{zh|黃碧蓮}}, born 1 January 1991) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] television presenter, actress and model currently based in [[Hong Kong]] under contract with [[TVB]].
==Early life== Huynh was born and raised in [[Vancouver]] where she attended [[Fraser Heights Secondary School]] (Source: https://www.facebook.com/linna.huynh.5) university at [[University of British Columbia]]. She is the second of four sisters. She started to model while attending high school, gaining experience with bridal, fashion and makeup modelling before entering a local modelling competition in 2010.
==Career==
===Modelling=== She first participated in the [[Miss Chinese (Vancouver) Pageant]] in 2012, securing the titles of Miss Most Photogenic and Miss Best Complexion. She is the first contestant in the history of the pageant to not secure a winning title after securing the aforementioned awards. She then participated in the [[Miss Hong Kong Pageant]] in 2014, placing in the Top Five, and being the runner-up for Miss Photogenic.<ref>[http://www.missosology.info/forum/viewtopic.php?f=5&t=462952&start=120 Miss Hong Kong 2014 Veronica Shiu]</ref> She later signed with TVB.
===Acting=== Huynh was the lead female actress in the Vancouver-based, Asian-styled action movie ''Beyond Redemption''.<ref>{{IMDb title|4059112|title=Beyond Redemption}}</ref>
She is currently a TV host at TVB, hosting [[Think Big (game show)|Think Big]] (天地), a children's game show,<ref>http://mytv.tvb.com/tc/cat_kids/ed_tvbkids/kidsthinkbig/260639</ref> as well as lifestyle program [[Dolce Vita (TV programme)|Dolce Vita]], home interior design programme 安樂蝸 Own Sweet Home, and Big Big Beauty 今期流行, in addition to TVBi Entertainent News show 1周八爪娛. Having limited skills speaking Cantonese, or reading and writing Chinese, Huynh has been assigned to working in variety programmes to further improve her Chinese before she is able to be considered for dramas.{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}
Linna was in the 28th Artiste Training Class hosted by TVB.<ref>http://artiste.tvb.com/main/artistedetail/huynhlinna</ref>
